  "text": "Next, we turn to the principal result of this section, the representation of \u03c6, \u03c8 1 , q, r in terms of Riemann theta function associated with K n , assuming n = (n \u2212 , n + ) \u2208 N 2 0 \\{(0, 0)} for the remainder of this section. In addition to (3.55) and (3.58), let \u2126 (2) P \u221e\u00b1 ,k and \u2126 [CITATION_1] P 0,\u00b1 ,k be the normalized differentials of the second kind with a unique pole at P \u221e\u00b1 and P 0,\u00b1 , respectively, and principal parts",
